law.catch_line: Contracts with federal government for federal aid in airport development.
law.text: The Kentucky Transportation Cabinet, any governmental unit, or the cabinet together with any governmental unit may contract with the federal government in regard to the development of airports under any Act of Congress providing federal aid to the states in airport development.
law.history: Amended 1960 Ky. Acts ch. 179, sec. 66, effective March 25, 1960. -- Created 1948 Ky. Acts ch. 239, sec. 3.
